200	  let summary = "Proxy for cudaq::qkernel.";
201	  let description = [{
202	    An entry-point kernel may take a reference to another kernel as an argument.
203	    The passed kernel may be entirely opaque at compile-time with its definition
204	    present in some other compilation module.
205	
206	    It is on the programmer to use the cudaq::qkernel type. This wrapper class
207	    is very much like std::function, but it extends that functionality with some
208	    extra information for the runtime to be able to "link" the distinct kernels
209	    on the device side and provide, for example, LTO at JIT compile time.
210	  }];
